eu.mf2c.security.ac.data

Class JsonJWE

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jose4j.jwx.JsonWebStructure
      • org.jose4j.jwe.JsonWebEncryption
        • eu.mf2c.security.ac.data.JsonJWE

  • public class JsonJWE
extends org.jose4j.jwe.JsonWebEncryption
    This class extends the JOSE4j JsonWebEncryption class. It adds methods for building a per-recipient Json web encryption object with general Json serialisation. The AEAD algorithm (AES-CBC-Hmac;) is used in an encrypt-then-MAC approach to encrypt the plain text payload using the AES/CBC/PKCS5Padding algorithm and a MAC is computed over the ciphertext, initialization vector, additional associated data (AAD) using the SHA2 algorithm. The key encryption key must be an RSA 2048 bit public key. The AAD is stored as part of the protected header. If the 'zip' header element is defined, the plain text payload is compressed using the RFC 1951 compression algorithm.

    author Shirley Crompton email shirley.crompton@stfc.ac.uk org Data Science and Technology Group, UKRI Science and Technology Council Created 20 Mar 2019 *
